env PAGER=cat man timing_extract_model_enable_unconstrained_port_m odelling
Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
timing_extract...port_modelling(25.10)  timing_extract...port_modelling(25.10)

Name
       timing_extract_model_enable_unconstrained_port_modelling

Syntax
       timing_extract_model_enable_unconstrained_port_modelling

        {true | false}

       Default: false

       Enables extraction of unconstrained paths to the output ports.

       When  set  to  false, for unconstrained output ports, which have no in-
       bound timing, there will be no arcs modelled for the paths.

       When set to true, the software will extract dummy arcs inbound  to  un-
       constrained output ports that will show the following characteristics:

              * Early  delay/slew  of last stage connected to the output ports
                will be modelled.

              * Related pins will be specified as unique unconstrained  inter-
                nal pins.

              * Extracted  slew  values  will  be  modelled  as unidimensional
                *_transition tables that are dependent on the  output  capaci-
                tance and real propagated slews inside a block.

              * Extracted  unidimensional  delays  will  be  displayed  in the
                cell_* tables.

       To set this global variable, use the set command.

Related Information
              * "Extracting Timing Models" chapter in the Innovus User Guide.

